          <msContents>
            <summary>Tiny manuscript, a kind of pocket book, for personal use, recitation, and prayer dedicated to the worship and praise of Hindu deity Gaṇeśa, the elephant-headed lord of obstacles. Praises the deity in eight verses (āṣṭika), although there are missing parts of verses four through six. Text is possibly derived from the Padmapurāṇa, Uttarakhaṇḍa.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Gaṇeśastotra</title>
              <title type="vernacular">गणेशस्तोत्र</title>
              <author>
